Siemens Enterprise Plans 6% Sales Growth, FT Deutschland Says

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-03-03T08:31:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/siemens-enterprise-plans-6-sales-growth-ft-deutschland-says.html
Siemens  Enterprise Communications ,
the call-center equipment business spun off from  Siemens AG (SIE) ,
aims to increase sales by more than 6 percent this year adjusted
for currency shifts,  Financial Times Deutschland  reported,
citing an interview with Chief Executive Officer Hamid Akhavan.  Profitability of the business that is owned 51 percent by
the Gores Group, LLC. and 49 percent by Siemens is “rising
enormously,” and sales increased in 2010, the newspaper cited
Akhavan as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Weiss in  Frankfurt  at 
 rweiss5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at   bkammel@bloomberg.net . 